subSubSection.paragraph:
Ectosomal skeleton
: The ectosomal skeleton of the sponge body is a thin membranous sheet covered with cleistochelae (
Figure 5 A
). The ectosomal skeletons of the filaments also include cleistochelae and abundant sigmancistras (
Figure 5 D
), whilst the ectosome of the stem only shows the remains of the cleistochelae (
Figure 5 C
).
